stimulus: Welcome to the experiment. Press any key to begin.

Instructions

In this experiment, you will see two random dot kinematograms (RDKs) simultaneously.

RDK consists of white dots or black dots moving in a specific direction.

Your task is to determine the direction of the target RDK based on the number of dots.

For instance, if the white RDK has more dots than the black RDK, the white RDK is the target so you should respond to the direction of the white RDK.

After viewing the RDKs, you will rotate a bar to indicate the perceived direction of the target RDK using the left and right arrow keys. Press Enter when you are ready to submit your response.

You will receive points based on the accuracy of your response. Try to be as accurate as possible!

You will have three practice trials. Press Enter key to start the practice phase.
